name: Camping nr 68 "Astur"
location: 22-232 Okuninka;, Poland
comments:
Lo consiglio. 
Cibo molto buono, italiano. Sistemazione in casette molto accoglienti vista mare (abbiate comunque spirito di adattamento perch√© sarete immersi nella natura quindi ci sono giustamente farfalle ecc ).
Animazione sempre gentile mai invadente. Il direttore Marco e il suo staff sono stati sempre professionali 
Consiglio: portate soldi cash perch√© c'√® solo una banca che non sempre funziona in caso voleste contanti ma cmq la struttura pu√≤ cambiarvi i soldi nella moneta locale. 
Andate a Playa Paradiso sono rimasto fulminato dalla sua bellezza, dista solo 5 m dal villaggio. 
Buone vacanze

Villaggio veramente ben tenuto e a dir poco meraviglioso. Le camere sono tutte dei bungalow con fronte mare. La cucina veramente ottima e bravissimo il cuoco a gestirsi con quello che gli arriva. Animazione presente ma non invadente formata da ragazzi giovani e con molta voglia di fare. Un grazie soprattutto a Any ed Eugenia per averci accompagnato in questa vacanza. Il posto √® meraviglioso sia per la spiaggia del villaggio che per playa sirena dove si svolgono le attivit√† del mattino.Fenomenale l'uscita in catamarano con il super reef davvero imperdibile come escursione. Unico neo della vacanza: aver fatto solo una settimana, ne avremo fatta volentieri una seconda. Se andate portate del tabacco da girare a Dax il capo animatore (pueblo) e accendini per i poveri animatori.
Piccolo ma funzionale. Lo consiglio perch√© √® molto ricco di servizi. La spiaggia del villaggio non √® il massimo... Ma tanto c'√® playa paraiso e soprattutto playa sirena!

Posto incantevole...ma le case hanno bisogno di una piccola sistemata visto che entrano gli scarafaggi...il sabato a causa degli arrivi e delle partenze,gli ospiti presenti sono stati del tutto trascurati. Lo staff di animazione √® discreto visto che avevano detto di liberare le tartarughe e non l'hanno fatto,giocare a beach volley in spiaggia e alla fine ho giocato con quelli del villaggio bravo, fare giochi di intrattenimento nel pomeriggio e invece ognuno si faceva i fatti propri. Unica nota del tutto positiva e che porter√≤ nel cuore sono il cuoco Nicola davvero bravo e la mitica animatrice Any,ci ha fatto divertire in ogni momento della giornata (anche nella sua giornata libera) ed era l'unica che si inventava qualcosa,nonostante l'assenza di musica a causa della morte di Fidel , da una semplice partita a carte ad una partita di pallavolo in piscina alla grande squadra mojto...

Posto incantevole mare stupendo, non posso dire della spiaggia che √® piccola , bisognava spostarsi a Baya Sirena , e l√† devo dire che √® un paradiso.... Animatori eccezionali tutti bellissima vacanza

name: Le≈õna Ryba Sp. z o.o.
location: Stara Jedlanka 23, 21-109 Stary U≈õcim√≥w, Poland
comments:
We had a great experience. The campground was all that we had hoped for and more. We camped in a Teardrop trailer and stayed for just one night. 
The new owners were friendly and helpful. The campsites were spacious and had many trees. There is a beautiful overlook to gather and view the ocean. The bathrooms are new and very nice. The showers were being renovated but they had outdoor showers that were new and spacious,... very well done!
We would stay there again for sure!

Our new favorite camping spot. Scott and Catherine (owners) were great! Great people and very accommodating. Amazing location on the ocean with spacious wooded sites. Best camp bathhouse shower I've ever experienced with super clean bathrooms. Looking forward to the lobster bake on the ocean tonight. The dogs loved it too! We will definitely be back!

We stayed for two nights over Memorial Day weekend and enjoyed it very much. The campground is under new ownership and it is awesome. The new owners, Kathryn and Scott, along with family  and friends are working really hard to make this the place to camp in Rockport, Maine. The views are outstanding. Loved the cedar showers. We wish them good luck and hope to be back in the Maine area in years to come to stay here again.

Love the people who frequent this place. So many wonderful people make this an annual destination. Warm, welcoming people at a wooded campground by the Sea! Quiet, family place in an amazing piece of the planet.  Spectacular!
Never camped there. Repaired the pool liner. Seemed to be an alright place. Depends on what you are looking for I guess.

name: Kemping "Zielona Dolina"
location: Ko≈õmin 7, 24-103 Ko≈õmin, Poland
comments:
My partner and I visited for the 1st weekend- this December,2016 to Jim Corbett- and absolutely everything about our stay at the resort was just perfect, and exceeded our expectations.

The room was beautiful with outstanding view, pebbled path leading to the cottage, thatched roofs, the atmosphere tranquil, and the great food.

But what really set the resort apart, and made our visit special, was the service. We were taken such good care of, by every one of the staff. We read countless reviews on this resort and all met or exceeded our expectations and  were not let down one bit! 

The place is amazing, the cottages are fantastic, food is great and the service was incredible! You can even tailor your own menu with the chef.
The holiday from start to finish was amazing- would recommend the place to anybody!
I would rate this resort  as 'excellent plus'! Hubs and I loved sitting on our balcony each morning drinking coffee.
Serene, peaceful and away from the hustle bustle.
Every one of the staff went above and beyond to make our stay special - with Mr. Ansari in particular going out of his way to make our stay special. Thanks for the memories!
Overall we had a good time and it is a great resort, we would certainly return.
Room Tip: Last Cottage(No 6) by the lazy river (River Kosi) is the best.

Good place to spend quality time with family and kids. Thanks To Mr. Ansari for providing home like food and soft spoken helpinv staff. 
A must visit place for all Camp RiverWild
We love Camp River wild  resort of Mr. Ansari & visit every year. Wonderful surroundings , excellent arrangement for stay & sumptuous food. Overall we always come back with a smiling face....
Excellent resort of 6 big cottages, awesome food and wonderful hospitality. A must for anyone travelling to Jim Corbett
Very good to spend 2 3 days
